---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
const lastUpdated = 'March 9, 2026';
---

<MainLayout locale={locale} title="FinDIT | Terms of Service">
  <article class="legal-shell">
    <header>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <p class="legal-intro">
      These Terms govern your use of FinDIT websites, apps, and related services. By using FinDIT, you agree to these
      Terms. FinDIT is currently operated by an independent product team and is not yet registered as a legal company
      entity.
    </p>

    <div class="legal-body">
      <section>
        <h2>1. Eligibility and Account Responsibility</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You must be legally allowed to use this service where you live.</li>
          <li>You are responsible for the accuracy of information you submit and for activity under your account.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Service Scope</h2>
        <p>
          FinDIT is a local-first video retrieval product. Features may change over time, including preview, beta, and
          experimental functions. We may add, remove, or modify features without prior notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Do not use FinDIT for unlawful activity or to violate rights of others.</li>
          <li>Do not attempt to reverse engineer, disrupt, or abuse the service infrastructure.</li>
          <li>Do not upload or process content you do not have rights to use.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          FinDIT branding, product design, software, and related site materials are protected by applicable intellectual
          property laws. These Terms do not transfer ownership to you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Pricing and Future Paid Plans</h2>
        <p>
          If paid plans are offered, pricing, billing terms, and plan features will be shown on the pricing page or
          in-product purchase flows. We may update pricing and plan structures in the future.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Your use of FinDIT is also subject to our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          FinDIT is provided on an “as is” and “as available” basis. We do not guarantee uninterrupted availability,
          error-free operation, or fitness for every workflow.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, FinDIT operators are not liable for indirect, incidental, special,
          consequential, or exemplary damages arising from your use of the service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We may suspend or terminate access if these Terms are violated, if abuse is detected, or if service operation
          requires it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Governing Terms</h2>
        <p>
          Until formal company registration is completed, these Terms are interpreted under laws applicable to the service
          operator at the time of the dispute, without limiting mandatory consumer protections that apply in your region.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For legal or support questions, contact <a href="mailto:support@findit.studio">support@findit.studio</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</MainLayout>
